The paper deals with privacy concerns in mobility-on-demand (MoD) systems, which are related to security and cryptography (cs.CR). The proposed method involves optimizing the assignment of vehicles to passengers, which can be achieved through machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI). The algorithm presented in the paper is scalable and efficient, which falls under the category of algorithms and complexity (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the use of superfluous vehicles in the system, which can be seen as a form of resource allocation (cs.SI). Overall, the paper covers a range of topics related to computer science, but the focus on privacy and optimization suggests that cs.CR and cs.AI are the most likely categories.
